# Wingman

**One-liner:** Test cold outbound on a digital twin of your real audience before you send a single one.

## Pipeline

1. **Fiber AI** — ICP in plain English → real live companies/people
2. **Orange Slice** — Enrich sample into personas (funding, pain signals, intent score)
3. **Custom swarm** (OpenAI GPT-4o, our code, NOT a fork) — persona agents react in character + reason + segment tag
4. **Live 3D graph** — react-force-graph-3d + bloom, clustered by segment, sentiment color, streams via Convex
5. **Score card** — predicted reply rate + top objection per segment
6. **Rewrite** — Cursor SDK (@cursor/sdk, composer-2, OpenAI fallback) fixes top objection, swarm re-runs once
7. **Send** — Orange Slice one-click to opt-in list

## Stack roles

- **Convex** — reactive backend; every reaction writes live, frontend subscribes
- **Next.js + Vercel** — deployed from hour one
- Full spec: `PROJECT_SPEC.md`

## Security (public repo)

- API keys ONLY in Convex env: `npx convex env set KEY value`
- Never bundle keys in client code or commit `.env*`
- Keys: `FIBER_API_KEY`, `ORANGESLICE_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `CURSOR_API_KEY`
- Client only needs `NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL` in `.env.local`
- Before commits: confirm no `.env*` files staged

## Code layout

- `/convex` — functions
- `/app` — routes
- `/components` — UI
- `/lib` — fiber.ts, orangeslice.ts, cursorSdk.ts, openai.ts

## Build rules

- Swarm engine is custom code inspired by mirofish, not forked
- Do not hallucinate API shapes — implement from real docs when wiring integrations
- Minimize scope; match existing conventions
